fo:block-container.fo:block:
Spatial data is expressed as latitude (​

    φ

)
and longitude (​

    λ

) geographic coordinates. Latitude values are stored as a negative number to represent a position south of the Equator. Longitude values are stored as a negative number to represent a position west of the International Prime Meridian. Coordinates are expressed as real value, degree / degree decimal format. Datasets conforming to this product specification are not projected.
